    Description

    Les Demoiselles d'Avignon is a large oil painting created in 1907 by the Spanish artist Pablo Picasso. Part of the permanent collection of the Museum of Modern Art in New York, it portrays five nude female prostitutes in a brothel on Carrer d'Aviny, a street in Barcelona, Spain. Wikipedia
    Artist: Pablo Picasso
    Location: The Museum of Modern Art
    Period: Cubism
    Created: 19071907
    Subject: Woman
    Medium: Oil paint
    Dimensions: 243.9 cm 233.7 cm (96 in 92 in)
